Package: libcritnib-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libcritnib0 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: ordered map data structure with lock-free reads
 Critnib is a data structure that provides a very fast equal and
 less-or-equal searches; it is a mix between DJBerstein's critbit
 and radix trees.  It works well on real-life data which forms
 spindly trees:
  * fully random: divergence on first bits
  * malloc addresses: clumps of bits in the middle
  * sequences: only lowest bits are filled
 .
 This library ships only u64->u64 mappings, optimized for reads
 from a very critical section but only limited writes.  Other
 variants also exist (such as fully lock-free writes, keys of
 arbitrary length), and can be included here upon request.

